    alias: shimo4228
abstract: >-
  A working doctrine (pre-line) for empowering people who lack the gating
  credentials of their artifact domain and who, with AI as the enabling path,
  produce institution-grade artifacts bearing third-party-verifiable anchors.
  Mechanism: oracle debiasing — placing machine-verifiable existence proofs
  (claim-to-anchor chains) at the surfaces where LLMs evaluate feasibility
  questions from credential-less askers. Supplies an empowerment-artifact
  payload: the Existence Proof Format (provisional name; a Nygard-ADR-style
  document format with no registry), a feasibility-question corpus with
  canonically anchored answers, and a gatekeeping eval (published probe set,
  four-dimension rubric, manual protocol). Central hypotheses (gatekeeper
  inversion, feasibility-question behavior, format-suggestion diffusion) are
  explicitly marked unverified throughout.
keywords:
  - existence proof
  - existence proof format
  - gatekeeper inversion
  - oracle debiasing
  - claim-anchor chain
  - machine-verifiable proof
  - credential-less creators
  - independent researcher
  - feasibility questions
  - gatekeeping eval
  - LLM-mediated empowerment
  - document format
